# Workspace Canvas Redesign

Redesign the workspace to feel like a real document editor (Notion-style) with a cleaner sidebar matching the messaging panel aesthetic.

## Proposed Changes

### WorkspaceEditor ([WorkspaceEditor.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceEditor.tsx))
- **Remove** the sticky `<header>` bar (title input + delete button) from the top
- **Add** a full-width editable title as the very first block on the canvas (large `contentEditable` h1 or Input, styled like a Notion page title)
- **Remove** the separate "note widget" concept from the context menu — the canvas itself is a text editor; clicking anywhere creates a text block
- The canvas `<div>` already uses `overflow-y-auto`. Add `overflow-x-auto` and `min-width: max-content` so blocks can expand horizontally
- Context menu keeps **Task widget** and **Table widget** insertion (+ converts to text block by default on Enter/click)
- [WidgetContainer](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/components/workspace/widgets/widget-container.tsx#20-89) grid-drag stays but also expands naturally as blocks overflow the viewport

### WorkspaceSidebar ([WorkspaceSidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceSidebar.tsx))
- Replace Notion-light-theme look with **dark panel style** matching the messages `ConversationList`
- Use `var(--bg-surface)` / `var(--bg-elevated)` / `var(--border)` CSS variables (same as the main app sidebar)  
- Each document row: icon avatar on left, document name + last-edited timestamp on right, active highlight with `var(--primary-muted)`
- Team/Teamspace rows: Use icon badge (emoji) + bold team name + member count, collapsible with chevron
- Remove the separate "Home / Inbox / Library" top-level items (not used in the app)
- Simplify search to a compact search bar matching the messages panel

### [widgets/types.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/components/workspace/widgets/types.ts)
- No change needed to types — [WidgetType](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/components/workspace/widgets/types.ts#1-2) stays as `'note' | 'task' | 'table'`

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Open [http://localhost:3001](http://localhost:3001) and log in with `admin@demo.com / Admin123!`
2. Navigate to **İşler/Panom** → click **Workspace** section in the sidebar
3. Open any document — verify there is **no sticky title header** at the top, just the canvas
4. Click anywhere on the dark grid canvas → verify a text block appears inline and is directly typeable
5. Right-click anywhere on the canvas → verify context menu shows **Görev Listesi** and **Veri Tablosu** (no note option)
6. Add a task widget → verify it renders correctly and is draggable (grab handle on hover)
7. Verify the document title is editable at the top of the canvas as a large heading
8. Check the left sidebar: verify it uses the dark app styling (not the old off-white Notion look), document rows show icons + names + timestamps
